      "id": 1,
      "text": "Rifton started as a handful of hamlets, with Dashville being the first settled community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rifton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1901 Rifton incorporated, uniting Rifton Glen, Swartekill, Dashville, Saltpeterville, and Perrine's Bridge.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rifton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Woodcrest Bruderhof, founded in 1954, still produces wooden toys while living communally in Rifton.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Rifton,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A cotton mill once grew into a large local enterprise, making Rifton a key manufacturing hub along the river system.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        9
